---
title: "_call (Caller)"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> q_call: (success, response) = target.call(data)
    q_call --> q_check_success: evaluate success
    q_check_success --> q_return: success == true
    q_check_success --> q_check_response: success == false
    q_check_response --> q_bubble_revert: response.length > 0
    q_check_response --> q_revert: response.length == 0
    q_bubble_revert --> [*]: revert(response)
    q_revert --> [*]: revert LowLevelCallFailed()
    q_return --> [*]: return response

    note right of q_call
        INV-001: target can be any address including contracts and EOAs
        INV-002: if success is false and response is non-empty, the original revert reason is preserved
        INV-003: if success is false and response is empty, LowLevelCallFailed is reverted
        INV-004: return data is only returned on successful call
    end note
